  						<table border='0' cellpadding='3' cellspacing='0' width='92%'>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>SWIFTTAIL, THE TALE OF SLEAT. CHAPTER 1, THE BEGINNING</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><P>Mir stands in the great arena he closes his eyes and feels each grain of sand under his bare feet; he curls his clawed toes and stretches his legs. His thick tail sways from side to side countering each movement of his body keeping him perfectly balanced.  He looks over at the warrior on his right, its rhino hide armor gleams a dull gray in the overcast sunlight, the warrior meets his gaze and smiles at Mir flexing his large arms and pointing at him. Mir shakes his head the warrior class has always been boisterous, Mir removes his silk robe bearing his back and chest, huge scars run across his body large knots of scar tissue tell the tales of many duels and battles, Mir turns and looks at the rhino clad warrior and smiles, the warriors face scales lay flat with respect and fear, the warrior quickly looks away.</P>
<P>Mir looks across the great arena two of each class is represented in the great brooding melee his eyes wander across the arena to his counter part a member of the taloned fist, the opposing monk looks at Mir and then looks away, Mir sits on the ancient sands and meditates, the battles will begin soon he feels the roar of the crowed as the shadow knight class contestants step forward each class will be allowed one winner before the grand melee will begins. Mir watches as the shadow knight hack at each other, their weapons and pets clash, the crowed goes wild as one of the shadow knights falls his skull smashed in, the remaining shadow knight limps back to his area to heal and rest. Next the wizards step forward they look across the arena never coming closer to each other, the air between the two combatants flares with fire and ice, the smell of ozone fills the arena suddenly one of the wizards screams and grabs his head magical fire shoots out of his eyes as he is consumed from the inside his body falls to the ground the smell of burning flesh and bones fills the air.</P>
<P>The arena is cleared of the dead the shaman are told to step fwd, as the battle commences the summoned pets ravage each other wolf hair and blood spill to the ground, the shaman sickening and poisoning as they cast finally a pet falls the surviving pet attacks the other shaman ripping and tearing, his attention drawn from his opponent to the attacking pet the shaman pierces the pet just as the other shaman lands a devastating spell the loosing shaman staggers and falls his skin bubbling from the scourge ravaging his body.</P>
<p>The surviving shaman limps back to his corner his scales pale with sickness.
The necromancers step fwd their pets attack with out warning hacking and slashing as their masters cast at each other, each necromancer staggering as the spells land. The power and evil magic’s fill the arena one of the necromancers falls to his knees, his pet falters and crumbles to the ground, the fallen necromancer his hands glow blue then sputter out, he looks up in disbelief as his opponents pets falls upon him slashing and striking, the Necromancer screams in pain as his life ends. The crowed goes wild; the pet walks away and joins his master as they walk back to their corner of the arena.</P>
<p>Mir watches each winner as he fights looking for weaknesses or failures he notes how long it takes to cast, the stamina and the fighting skill of each class.</p>
<p>Mir looks up and sees the warrior studying him, he smiles at the warrior the warrior winks at him and steps forward as the warriors are called to battle.</p> 
<p>Mir studies the warrior intently this will be one of the fastest contests yet, the warriors approach each other bow and draw their weapons, steel on steel clang as their weapons meet in silver arcs, the fight begins.
Mir watches with a trained eye as the battle ends as fast as it started, the warriors head hits the ground before its body knows its gone, It crumples to the ground, Mir watches as the rhino clad warrior walks back to his corner his weapon held high over his head the blood of his fallen opponent dripping down the blade across his hand he screams a battle yell to the crowed and bows.</p> 
<p>Mir nods at the warrior acknowledging a job well done, he rises as his class is called he steps into the arena the warm sand feels good on his feet, he hefts his batons, his silken wu pants flows over his legs he slows his breathing, he feels the calming effects of his teaching. He looks at his foe close for the first time his scaled chest is clean not one scar mars its surface, Mir wonders either he has never lost a duel or never fought to earn his scars. </p>
<p>Mir stands across from his foe, they watch each other each one waiting for the other to move, Mir sees a flicker of movement as his foes fist flashes past his head his slight movement paying off his secondary eye lids snap shut his vision snaps to perfect clarity his fighting gland spills massive amounts adrenaline into his body
He slams his baton into his foes head with a wet thunk, the monk staggers Mir presses his attack slamming his baton on top of his foes shoulder he smiles as he hears bones snap, and a pained hiss emanates from his foe as he staggers away.</p>
<p>Mir steps back he watches as the monks body shaking in pain, his arm hanging useless along his side, moves keeping his weak side away from Mir, Mir lunges causing the monk to move to the right he steps into Mir’s heel as he uses a spinning kick crushing the monks throat, Mir whips his baton out in a deadly golden arch smashing the thin temporal bones and driving them into his brain, the monk crashes to the ground his eyes hazed over his legs twitching and kicking up sand as the dead monks hearts slowly stops pumping.
 Mir stands and wills his hearts to slow down, his scales flicker and smooth as he calms down, his fighting lids snap open flooding his eyes with light, he walks back to his corner ignoring the roar of the crowed, he looks over at the rhino clad warrior, the battle lasted less than 30 seconds.
The warrior nods at Mir, he sits and meds soon after the sun has reached its peak the grand melee will begin…</p>
<p>As the crowds gather for the grand melee the brood females are paraded thru the arena, each female proving her prowess in the games held months before, they are stripped of all clothing, their once thin whip like tails are now fat and thick soon they will go into heat.
Mir looks on with little interest unless they are in heat he cannot feel anything towards them.</p>
<p>The horns sound for the grand melee, he stands and bows to the rhino clad warrior next to him he will fight the best of the classes today it is a test worthy of his skills, the warrior returns the bow he raises his sword to Mir and hisses at him in brotherly praise, the second horn sounds they have each drawn for the right of opponents Mir has drawn the shadow knight, he walks to his foe ignoring the others they will come next the third horn sounds the shadow knight attacks swinging his mace at Mir’s head, he easily side steps and smashes his baton into the back of the shadow knights neck crushing vertebras  the shadow knight drops his mouth gasping for air that will never come. He jumps on the back of the shadow knights pet grabbing its cold fleshless skull in his hands he twists, the pet falls into a pile of bones and dust as its head snaps off in Mir's hands</p>
<p>Mir spins he picks his next foe the wizard stands over the necromancer his dagger buried in its chest. Mir leaps, landing a flying kick against the wizard’s chest feeling ribs popping he crushes the wizards skull with his baton, silencing his spell before it even starts.</p>
<p>Mir turns as the warrior dispatches the shaman running him thru with his sword, the warrior presses his foot to the dead shamans chest yanking the sword free he turns and bows to Mir, Mir mirrors the warriors bow, they circle each other the warriors shield and sword weave in and out always moving, trying to keep Mir guessing where the attack will come from, the monk waits.</p>
<p>With a blinding swing the warriors sword whips out, and is blocked with Mir’s baton, Mir hisses with surprise as his baton is forced from his grip, the warrior disarming him with a clean sweep. The warrior moves to the left thinking Mir will go for his lost weapon Mir strikes out with his one baton stunning the warriors shield arm the shield drops from the warriors grip his arm hanging at his side, Mir now off balance with only one baton throws it to the corner, he will use his bare hands to fight, the way he has trained all his life the way his masters fought in the days of old.</p>
<p>The warrior circles him his sword always moving, darting here and there looking for a weakness, Mir watches the warrior he shows so much skill to use a slashing weapon with such clean swift thrust, Mir thinks he is a worthy foe it is a shame to kill him. The warrior lunges and slashes at the same time Mir hisses in pain as he feels the scales on his back open up from the edge of the warriors blade and blood runs down his back, Mir shivers at the wonderful pain his senses heighten, he waits for the warrior to poke at him one last time and steps forward in one swift step, he feels the power of the dragon punch build in his body and strikes punching into the armored chest, Mir hisses in pain as the bones in his fingers shatter and the skin of his fist explodes against the hardened armor, he steps back the warrior looks at Mir’s ruined bloody hand and opens his mouth to laugh, no air leaves his body he looks down his armor is dented and torn right over the apex of his 2 hearts, the warrior drops his weapons and clutches his chest, he cannot feel his hearts beating.</p>
<p>Mir watches as the warrior falls to his knees his punch having torn his hearts from their cartilage mounts ripping them with the force of the punch. Mir spins, his leg whips out hitting the warriors helmed head all goes dark for the warrior as he hears a couple loud pops his spine snapping in two, Mir kills him so he will not suffer he deserves a warriors death.</p>
<p>The crowed roars Mir looks for his next victim all he sees are dead bodies he has won, the grand melee is over.
Mir is carried thru the streets his wounds are healed with the most powerful shaman magic’s.
He will heal for two days then he will enter the brooding chambers, he meditates for hours.</P>
<p>After 2 days his new battle approaches, the 25 females have gone into heat; a cadre of female warriors each picked for her prowess and skill guards them.
The females prowl the brooding pits angry and ready, Mir is lead into the pits he feels the scent of the females pulling on his mind the basic animal in him takes over his body, he is no longer Mir of the Swifttails he is the alpha male, and this is his brood, they gather around him the smell is over whelming the door to the pits are closed………………. 10 days later Mir huddles in the corner of one of the sub tunnels his body is thin and frail he as not seen the sun or eaten for days, he can hardly walk his legs and lower body are bruised and torn . He can hear them looking for him each female her egg sacks swelling and growing fatter each day are hunting for him, the mating scent has all but left the chamber each female falling out of heat as her eggs drop they now hunt him down for food. He doesn’t have the strength to fight his body used up as the breeding madness overtook him, burning once well-trained muscles for energy. He shivers in the cool caverns; he looks up to see the females looking over him. He doesn’t even have the strength to hiss in fear as they attack him………………………………………</p>
 </font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><small>By <b>Lyrak</b> Submited on 10/17/2001</small></td>
